.SH "RETURN VALUE
A 0 value is returned on success.  A \-1 value indicates
an error.
.SH "ERRORS
The \fIfsync\fP fails if:
.TP 15
[EBADF]
\fIFd\fP is not a valid descriptor.
.TP 15
[EINVAL]
\fIFd\fP refers to a socket, not to a file.
